name: How can my players even have a chance at resolving this Tomb of Horrors puzzle?
content:
8
down vote
accepted
Each of the seven doors is opened by one method, not all seven.

The text in the 5th edition is ambigious, and may be interpreted that each door requires a seven-step process to open. However, if you look at the map, each door is lettered, making it clearer that, for example, step "A" is the method for opening the door "A", step "B" the second door, and so on.

This is made much clearer in the original AD&D module:

Each of these portals must be opened by hand, and each requires a different method of opening.

The D&D 3.5 version concurs:

However, each secret door is marked on the map by a letter indicating the unique method whereby the door is opened. Each method differs from that of the previous door.

Further, it makes this note, defending the use of trial-and-error rather than skill checks:

Note: Contemporary D&D rules don't normally support the minutia involved in how a particular secret door is opened; however, the essence of this secret door complex requires this level of attention to avoid making the navigation of this area nothing more than a mathematical exercise.

name: How many agents can I add?
content: You can add as many agents you want in the premium (Growth and Enterprise) plans. You will be charged per agent basis. In the Free plan, you can not add more than 2 agents.

name: How to upgrade or downgrade the plan?
content: You can drop us a line and we'll be happy to assist you in upgrading and downgrading your plan. In case of upgrading from Free to Growth plan, you can just go to Dashboard→Billing to update your account.

name: Can we host data on our server?
content: Yes, as part of Enterprise plan, we can deploy the solution at your servers and you will have complete control over the data.

name: Do you offer discounts for using it in multiple websites and apps?
content: Yes, get in touch with us here.

name: Is there any limit on the number of messages exchanged?
content: No, you can exchange as many messages as you want. Just make sure you stick to our Fair Usage Policy.

name: How does the 30 days trial work?
content: You can sign up for free to avail the benefits of the full-fledged support platform for 30 days. Credit card details are not required for the trial period. Post the 30 days period, you can upgrade to your preferred plan or else you will be automatically downgraded to the Free plan. We will not terminate the services.

name: Is it GDPR compliant?
content: Yes, we adhere to the GDPR compliances. To learn more about how we collect, store and process the data, please check out our Terms of Use.

name: Is there a free plan?
content: Yes, we do have a free forever plan. It comes with basic live chat and you can add up to 2 agents.

name: How can I use bots in chat?
content: You can easily add bots in live chat. Refer to our docs to know more about bot configuration.

name: What kind of pre-defined bots I can use?
content: We automatically add Liz, our FAQ bot, when you sign up. You can assign all conversation to Liz from conversation routing so that Liz can reply. You can also train Liz with more questions and answers by adding more FAQs from dashboard. If you have any other bot use case, let us know.

name: Can I request a custom bot as per my requirements?
content: Yes. You can request a custom bot to made fitting your requirements. Go to Dashboard→ Bot Integration and click on ‘Request a custom bot’. Just submit your custom use case in your requirements and we will get back to you.

name: What kind of integrations do you support?
content: We currently support integrations with CRMs, ticketing softwares, knowledge base Software, contact enrichment platforms, bot building frameworks. Some of the available integration are: Zendesk, Clearbit, Helpdocs, Agile CRM, Dialogflow etc. For using these products with Kommunicate, go to Dashboard→ Integrations. Please note that the Bot builder platforms are listed in Dashboard→ Bot Integration section.

name: How can I create FAQs?
content: You can easily create FAQs using Kommunicate. Go to Dashboard→ FAQ and click on ‘Add a FAQ’. You can fill your question and answer and choose to save as draft for publishing later or instantly publish your FAQs. Additionally, if you are using knowledge base softwares like Helpdocs. You can also integrate Helpdocs to fetch FAQs from the platform.

name: How to use FAQs in chat?
content: If you add any FAQ, the FAQ button on the chat will automatically be active. You can also assign all conversation to Liz,our FAQ bot, she will take care of FAQs.

name: Is there a way to automate answers for generic and recurring customer queries?
content: You can use Quick Replies to create templated messages for generic user queries. Go to Dashboard → Setting and click on Quick Replies under Team section. Click on ‘Create Shortcut’ and enter shortcut name and full message to be displayed. One example could be using ‘bot’ as message shortcut for ‘Are you looking for bot integration? We can help you. You can use Kommunicate’s Dialogflow integration to make your bot or request a custom bot from us’. You can trigger this message in chat by sending a message preceded by slash(/) and shortcut name. ‘/bot’ in aforementioned case.

name: What is conversation routing?
content: You can use conversation routing to apply a set of rules to assign conversations to your team members. You can either choose to notify everybody (recommended for small teams) or automatically assign conversations to agents on a round robin basis. ‘Notify Everybody’ option will send notifications to all team member and whosoever acts first, will be assigned the conversation.

name: How do I add team members?
content: You can add team member by inviting them from the Dashboard. Go to Dashboard→ Settings and click on ‘Teammates’ under the ‘Team’ section. Just enter the emails of your team members, assign their roles and we will send them a invitation to join the your team. Please note that your billing will automatically change once you update the number of agents you have.

name: How do I remove an agent?
content: You can delete an agent from the Dashboard→Teammates section. Just hover over the profile of the agent you want to delete and select ‘Delete’.

name: How do I create a ticket in Zendesk after integrating it?
content: You can send any conversation to Zendesk as a ticket. In Dashboard→ Conversations, click on Zendesk button below the message bar. Enter the conversation title and note and click on ‘Create Zendesk ticket’ button. This will create a ticket in Zendesk with submitted details.

name: Where do conversations go after I close them?
content: If you close any conversation, it moves to the ‘Closed’ section. You can reopen the closed conversations from the ‘Closed’ section as well. Also, if your customer replies to any closed conversation the conversation automatically reopens.

name: How can I collect email information from visitors when I my team is offline?
content: Kommunicate facilitates email data collection when your agents are offline. Go to Dashboard → Settings and click on Away Message under the Team section. While configuring your away message, check the box which says ‘Collect email ID from customer’ and we will do the rest.

name: How can I integrate Kommunicate in my Squarespace website?
content: You can integrate Kommunicate chat plugin in your Squarespace website without technical knowledge as well. Detailed instruction are given here.

name: How can I integrate Kommunicate in my Wix website?
content: You can integrate Kommunicate chat plugin in your Wix website without technical knowledge as well. Detailed instruction are given here.

name: How can I integrate Kommunicate in my Shopify website?
content: You can integrate Kommunicate chat plugin in your Shopify website without technical knowledge as well. Detailed instruction are given here.

name: Can I integrate Kommunicate in my native apps?
content: Yes, we provide you customizable SDKs for both Android and iOS platforms. Read more about integrating Kommunicate in your native apps here.

name: Can I integrate Kommunicate in my hybrid apps?
content: Yes, Kommunicate can be integrated in apps built on hybrid platforms such as Ionic, React Native, PhoneGap, and Xamarin. You can check out the detailed instruction in the docs.

name: How does Kommunicate pricing work?
content: Our pricing is based on number of seats. You will be charged for the number of seats you buy. Every addition and removal of agent will update your pricing. In case of monthly billing, you will be charged on the basis of number of agents you have at the start of billing date.

name: What happens when I delete agents in between my billing period?
content: If you delete agents before your next billing date, your number of seats will be reduced by the same number. Your next bill will be automatically adjusted on the basis of number of agents you have deleted. For example, you have 10 agents at the start of the billing period. If you delete 3 agents in between your billing period, you will only be charged for 7 agents from the next billing period.

name: What happens when I add agents in between my billing period?
content:
For monthly billing, if you add any number of agents in between your billing period, you will incur a prorated charge based on date of addition in your next bill. For example, suppose your billing cycle starts from 1st of each month and you have 10 agents. If you add any agent on 15th, in your next billing cycle, you will be charged for 11 agents + 15 days’ prorated charge for the new addition.

For yearly billing, if you add any agent in any month between your billing cycle, you will incur a prorated charge based on the number of month remaining and the billing will be updated with the latest number of agents from next cycle. For example, your yearly billing cycle starts from Jan 1st and you have 10 agents. If you add a agent in 3rd month, you will be charged for 9 remaining month instantaneously (yearly discounts will be applied). From your next billing cycle, you will be charged for 11 agents.

name: What happens when I have more seats than the number of agents?
content: If you have more seats than the number of agents you have added, you can fill the deficit by adding more agents. Your billing will not to changed if the agent count matched the number of seats after adding new agents. Alternatively, you can reduce the number of seats from the Billing section.

name: What happens when I have more agents than the number of seats?
content: If, in case you have more agents than the number of seats in your plan, the extra agents will not be able to login. The agents will be deactivated based on their chronological order.

qwerqer qwer

Searcharoo 4 added non-text filetypes (e.g. Word, PDF and Powerpoint), better robots.txt support and a remote-indexing console app.

Searcharoo 5 runs in Medium Trust and refactored FilterDocument into DownloadDocument and its subclasses for indexing Office 2007 files.

Searcharoo 6 adds indexing of photos/images and geographic coordinates; and displaying search results on a map.
